WEBVTT

00:01.697 --> 00:02.741
[Mindy]
PEOPLE ALWAYS ASK ME

00:02.785 --> 00:04.743
WHY I LIKE ROMANTIC COMEDIES
SO MUCH.

00:04.787 --> 00:06.180
IF I HADN'T BEEN FOX BOOKS,

00:06.223 --> 00:09.705
AND YOU HADN'T BEEN
THE SHOP AROUND THE CORNER,

00:09.748 --> 00:12.708
AND YOU AND I
HAD JUST MET...

00:12.751 --> 00:14.536
I KNOW.
YEAH.

00:14.579 --> 00:17.017
[Mindy]
IT'S BECAUSE EVEN UNDER
EXTRAORDINARY CIRCUMSTANCES,

00:17.060 --> 00:19.367
THE RIGHT TWO PEOPLE
CAN END UP TOGETHER.

00:19.410 --> 00:21.195
GUYS, TODAY SOMEONE
FROM MY PAST

00:21.238 --> 00:22.761
IS TAKING ME OUT TO LUNCH.

00:22.805 --> 00:24.285
WHO, YOUR UNCLE?YES, DANNY.

00:24.328 --> 00:25.590
I'M WEARING
THIS REALLY COOL OUTFIT

00:25.634 --> 00:27.331
FOR MY UNCLE FROM DENVER.

00:27.375 --> 00:28.593
ANYWAY, OVER THE WEEKEND,

00:28.637 --> 00:30.682
I WAS ADDING SOME PHOTOS
TO FACEBOOK...

00:30.726 --> 00:33.207
TO AN ALBUM CALLED
"GONE SNACKING,"

00:33.250 --> 00:34.208
WHEN A PICTURE OF A HOT DOG

00:34.251 --> 00:36.340
WAS LIKED
BY A GUY NAMED SAM,

00:36.384 --> 00:38.603
AS IN SAM KLEINFELD.

00:38.647 --> 00:39.604
OOH!
AH!

00:39.648 --> 00:41.215
[Mindy]
WHEN I WAS 13,

00:41.258 --> 00:43.347
MY ONE DREAM IN LIFE
WAS TO GO TO SLEEPAWAY CAMP.

00:43.391 --> 00:45.436
MY PARENTS SAID NO

00:45.480 --> 00:46.872
'CAUSE THEY WERE WORRIED
I'D GET MOLESTED,

00:46.916 --> 00:48.048
WHICH IS CRAZY,

00:48.091 --> 00:49.136
'CAUSE I WAS NOT
THAT CUTE A KID.

00:49.179 --> 00:50.572
FINALLY, THEY AGREED,

00:50.615 --> 00:53.401
BUT ONLY IF IT WAS
JEWISH SLEEPAWAY CAMP.

00:53.444 --> 00:55.055
CAMP TAKANAE.

00:55.098 --> 00:58.058
IF I WAS GOING TO BE AWAY
FROM HOME FOR SEVERAL WEEKS,

00:58.101 --> 01:00.190
MY PARENTS ONLY TRUSTED ME
IN THE GENTLE HANDS

01:00.234 --> 01:02.192
OF THE JEWS
OF THE BERKSHIRE MOUNTAINS.

01:02.236 --> 01:03.454
HI.

01:03.498 --> 01:05.456
EVERYONE WANTS TO KNOW
WHY YOU'RE HERE.

01:05.500 --> 01:07.545
ARE YOU EVEN JEWISH?

01:07.589 --> 01:08.938
FOR YOUR INFORMATION,

01:08.981 --> 01:11.288
CAMP TAKANAE HAS BEEN OPEN
TO NON-JEWISH CAMPERS

01:11.332 --> 01:15.205
SINCE THE LANDMARK 1989 CASE
CHAN VERSUS TAKANAE.

01:15.249 --> 01:16.337
AND THAT'S WHEN I MET HIM.

01:16.380 --> 01:17.903
SURE, SHE'S JEWISH,
TONY.

01:17.947 --> 01:20.036
SHE'S JUST SEPHARDIC.

01:20.080 --> 01:21.342
NO, I'M NOT.

01:21.385 --> 01:22.995
WAIT.
WHAT IS THAT?

01:23.039 --> 01:24.301
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.
THE JOKE LANDED.

01:24.345 --> 01:26.390
I'M SAM.HI, I'M MINDY.

01:26.434 --> 01:27.957
DO YOU WANT TO SEE A PIECE
OF THE BERLIN WALL?

01:28.000 --> 01:29.350
CHECK THIS OUT.

01:29.393 --> 01:31.395
WHOA.
[laughs]

01:31.439 --> 01:32.831
THAT'S GONNA BE WORTH
$1 MILLION SOMEDAY.

01:32.875 --> 01:34.659
[Mindy]
I DON'T THINK
I EVER LAUGHED MORE

01:34.703 --> 01:36.444
THAN WHEN I WAS HANGING OUT
WITH SAM THAT SUMMER.

01:36.487 --> 01:39.273
[laughs]
HE SOUNDS HILARIOUS.

01:39.316 --> 01:40.622
WHAT ARE YOU
BASING THAT ON?

01:40.665 --> 01:42.058
WELL, SHE SAID
HE'S JEWISH.

01:42.102 --> 01:43.407
MORGAN, WE'RE IN
THE MIDDLE OF MANHATTAN,

01:43.451 --> 01:44.626
FOR GOD'S SAKE.

01:44.669 --> 01:46.454
BUT IF YOU GUYS HAD
SUCH A DEEP CONNECTION,

01:46.497 --> 01:47.803
WHY DIDN'T YOU STAY
IN TOUCH?

01:47.846 --> 01:50.066
BETSY, WE WERE 13.
WE DIDN'T KNOW ANY BETTER.

01:50.110 --> 01:51.415
YOU DIDN'T EVEN EMAIL?

01:51.459 --> 01:53.156
EMAIL WAS NOT INVENTED YET.WHAT ABOUT FACEBOOK?

01:53.200 --> 01:54.897
FACEBOOK WASN'T
REALLY A THING YET.

01:54.940 --> 01:56.203
HOW OLD ARE YOU?

01:56.246 --> 01:57.291
I'M FINE. I'M YOUNG.

01:57.334 --> 01:58.292
DON'T WORRY ABOUT ME, OKAY?

01:58.335 --> 01:59.945
YEAH, THESE FACEBOOK
CONNECTIONS,

01:59.989 --> 02:01.121
THEY RARELY PAN OUT.

02:01.164 --> 02:02.339
I ONCE THOUGHT
I WAS GOING TO MEET

02:02.383 --> 02:03.601
A WELSH SUPERMODEL.

02:03.645 --> 02:05.603
NEXT THING I KNOW,
I'M HAVING A ROMANTIC DINNER

02:05.647 --> 02:07.953
WITH A MAN WITH NO TORSO.
UGH.

02:07.997 --> 02:09.868
I WAS CATFISHED
BEFORE CATFISH.

02:09.912 --> 02:11.783
WELL, I HOPE HE'S GREAT.THANKS, MORGAN.

02:11.827 --> 02:13.045
AND IT BREAKS MY HEART,

02:13.089 --> 02:14.264
SOME OF THE SLIMEBALLS
YOU'VE BEEN WITH.

02:14.308 --> 02:15.526
I'D LIKE YOU TO BE
LESS INVESTED.

02:15.570 --> 02:17.137
BUT YEAH,
IF HE IS ANYTHING

02:17.180 --> 02:19.400
LIKE THE WAY HE WAS
WHEN HE WAS 13, SURE.

02:19.443 --> 02:21.489
I CAN SEE US HAVING
A REAL RELATIONSHIP.

02:21.532 --> 02:22.925
YOU WANT TO DATE
A 13-YEAR-OLD?

02:22.968 --> 02:24.492
I DON'T WANT TO DATE
A 13-YEAR-OLD.

02:24.535 --> 02:26.146
IT COULD WORK.
YOU LIKE THE SAME MUSIC.

02:26.189 --> 02:28.670
[Sam]
HI, I'M LOOKING
FOR MINDY LAHIRI.

02:28.713 --> 02:30.628
HI.

02:30.672 --> 02:31.934
HEY, SAM.

02:31.977 --> 02:35.503
HE DOESN'T LOOK JEWISH.

02:35.546 --> 02:38.506
[upbeat music]

02:38.549 --> 02:46.557
♪

02:50.431 --> 02:53.173
IT IS, UM,
SO GOOD TO SEE YOU.

02:53.216 --> 02:55.697
I WISH I COULD SEE YOU,
BUT...I'M BLIND NOW.

02:55.740 --> 02:57.133
OH, MY GOD.

02:57.177 --> 02:58.134
I'M NOT ACTUALLY BLIND.

02:58.178 --> 02:59.222
THAT'S A WEIRD JOKE TO MAKE.

02:59.266 --> 03:00.876
I DON'T KNOW WHY I DID THAT.
I'M SORRY.

03:00.919 --> 03:02.791
I WAS NERVOUS TO SEE YOU,
SO I THOUGHT I'D DO A BIT.

03:02.834 --> 03:04.227
UH, OKAY.

03:04.271 --> 03:05.228
YOU LOOK THE SAME,
HONESTLY,

03:05.272 --> 03:07.099
WHICH IS VERY NICE.

03:07.143 --> 03:09.014
HEY, ANY FRIEND OF DR. LAHIRI'S
IS A BOSS OF MINE.

03:09.058 --> 03:10.842
COOL.LET ME GRAB THIS COAT
FOR YOU.

03:10.886 --> 03:12.714
OH, YOU'RE TAKING MY COAT OFF.OH, I LOVE YOUR T-SHIRT.

03:12.757 --> 03:14.324
DID YOU GET THAT
AT URBAN OUTFITTERS?

03:14.368 --> 03:17.022
OH, NO.
I GOT IT FROM THE ARMY.

03:17.066 --> 03:19.199
THEY GIVE YOU THEM
FOR FREE WHEN YOU JOIN.

03:19.242 --> 03:20.330
I JUST GOT BACK
FROM AFGHANISTAN.

03:20.374 --> 03:21.418
I GOTTA TELL YOU,

03:21.462 --> 03:23.028
I'VE BEEN A BIG FAN
OF SEAL TEAM 6

03:23.072 --> 03:24.378
WAY BEFORE YOU GUYS
KILLED BIN LADEN.

03:24.421 --> 03:27.032
COOL.
I'M NOT IN SEAL TEAM 6.

03:27.076 --> 03:29.034
I GOT YOU.
YOU'RE NOTIN SEAL TEAM 6.

03:29.078 --> 03:30.166
I'M REALLY NOT.
I HEAR YOU.

03:30.210 --> 03:31.733
THANK YOU.YOU'RE WELCOME.

03:31.776 --> 03:34.039
SAM, I'M DANNY.HEY.

03:34.083 --> 03:35.563
THANK YOU SO MUCH
FOR YOUR SERVICE.

03:35.606 --> 03:37.391
CAN SOMEONE GET THIS GUY
A SANDWICH?

03:37.434 --> 03:39.654
AND NOT A WRAP, AN ACTUAL
SANDWICH ON REAL BREAD.

03:39.697 --> 03:40.785
AWESOME.

03:40.829 --> 03:42.047
THAT'S WHAT
YOU'RE FIGHTING FOR.

03:42.091 --> 03:43.962
I'LL KEEP THAT IN MIND
WHILE I'M TAKING FIRE.

03:44.006 --> 03:45.094
I KNOW YOU WILL.

03:45.137 --> 03:47.401
YEAH.

03:47.444 --> 03:49.229
SO IF YOU DON'T
MIND ME ASKING,

03:49.272 --> 03:50.926
IT MUST BE PRETTY
CHALLENGING FOR YOU

03:50.969 --> 03:52.406
TO ACCLIMATE
TO CIVILIAN LIFE.

03:52.449 --> 03:54.016
IT WAS PRETTY WEIRD.YEAH.

03:54.059 --> 03:55.713
I GOT TO BE TOTALLY HONEST.
YEAH.

03:55.757 --> 03:57.411
THERE'S EVEN MORE SINGING
COMPETITION SHOWS NOW?

03:57.454 --> 03:59.848
THAT ACTUALLY
SPOOKED ME OUT FOR A SECOND.

03:59.891 --> 04:01.371
YOUR HAIR'S PRETTY LONG.

04:01.415 --> 04:02.372
FOR THE MILITARY, YEAH.

04:02.416 --> 04:03.808
THIS HAPPENS IN, LIKE,
TWO WEEKS.

04:03.852 --> 04:05.897
WHOA.VERY GOOD METABOLISM.

04:05.941 --> 04:07.159
[laughs]

04:07.203 --> 04:08.813
YOU'RE SO DIFFERENT, SAM,

04:08.857 --> 04:10.162
THAN HOW I REMEMBER YOU.

04:10.206 --> 04:11.947
SERIOUSLY,
YOU'RE NOT WHAT I THOUGHT.

04:11.990 --> 04:14.384
I THOUGHT YOU'D BE, LIKE,
A BORING MOM WITH THREE KIDS.

04:14.428 --> 04:15.951
YOU'D BE SHOWING ME PICTURES

04:15.994 --> 04:18.301
OF, LIKE, YOUR BABIES RIDING
YOUR DOG OR SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

04:18.345 --> 04:19.737
I DIDN'T THINK THAT IT'D BE,
YOU KNOW,

04:19.781 --> 04:21.261
YOU'RE A PRETTY DOCTOR.

04:21.304 --> 04:22.871
THANK YOU.

04:22.914 --> 04:24.481
YOU EVER GET YOUR PERIOD?

04:24.525 --> 04:26.396
THAT WAS A BIG THING
LAST TIME WE TALKED.

04:26.440 --> 04:27.397
[laughs]

04:27.441 --> 04:29.747
WE DECIDED TO TAKE
YOUR ADVICE

04:29.791 --> 04:31.140
AND USE A SPERM DONOR.

04:31.183 --> 04:32.272
FANTASTIC.

04:32.315 --> 04:33.316
WHO'S THE GUY?

04:33.360 --> 04:34.491
HE'S HANDSOME

04:34.535 --> 04:37.189
WITH THE CLASS
OF A YOUNG ROBERT DUVALL.

04:37.233 --> 04:39.801
AND THE GRAVITAS
OF AN OLD ROBERT DUVALL.

04:39.844 --> 04:40.845
[Danny]
AMAZING.

04:40.889 --> 04:42.673
DID YOU TALK
TO THIS GUY ALREADY?

04:42.717 --> 04:45.589
ACTUALLY, WE'RE DOING IT
RIGHT NOW.

04:45.633 --> 04:49.027
WAIT, YOU WANT...

04:49.071 --> 04:52.379
MY GUYS?

04:52.422 --> 04:54.381
HERE YOU GO. [woman]
THANK YOU.

04:54.424 --> 04:56.383
SO, WHAT ARE YOU
GONNA DO NOW?

04:56.426 --> 04:57.732
LIKE, GO MEET UP
WITH YOUR GIRLFRIEND

04:57.775 --> 04:58.733
AND MAKE OUT WITH HER?

04:58.776 --> 05:00.169
WHAT?

05:00.212 --> 05:01.605
I WAS TRYING TO FIND OUT
DURING LUNCH

05:01.649 --> 05:03.215
IF YOU HAD A GIRLFRIEND.

05:03.259 --> 05:05.348
OH. THAT'S THE BEST
YOU COULD COME UP WITH?

05:05.392 --> 05:07.350
[laughs]
THAT'S LAME.

05:07.394 --> 05:08.960
YOUR BOYFRIEND MUST
ALWAYS MAKE FUN OF YOU

05:09.004 --> 05:10.919
FOR SAYING--
YOU'RE RIGHT.

05:10.962 --> 05:13.008
IT'S ACTUALLY REALLY HARD
TO DO THAT ORGANICALLY.

05:13.051 --> 05:14.096
[woman]
HERE YOU GO.

05:14.139 --> 05:15.315
THANK YOU.

05:15.358 --> 05:16.925
YEAH.

05:16.968 --> 05:19.144
I DON'T HAVE A BOYFRIEND.I DON'T HAVE A GIRLFRIEND.

05:19.188 --> 05:21.364
I HAVE SIX KIDS THOUGH.

05:21.408 --> 05:23.192
[laughs]
SHUT UP.

05:23.235 --> 05:24.280
I DON'T KNOW ABOUT THIS,
GUYS.

05:24.324 --> 05:25.542
WE DON'T WANT
TO PRESSURE YOU,

05:25.586 --> 05:29.372
BUT YOU'D BE GIVING US
THE GREATEST GIFT.

05:29.416 --> 05:32.462
WE'D BE SO LUCKY IF OUR SON
TURNED OUT LIKE YOU.

05:32.506 --> 05:34.334
OKAY.

05:34.377 --> 05:36.379
[gasps]OKAY.

05:36.423 --> 05:37.380
I'LL DO IT.

05:37.424 --> 05:39.991
SEE, HONEY?
THAT WAS EASY.

05:41.428 --> 05:42.385
[Mindy]
OF ALL THE PLACES IN NEW YORK,

05:42.429 --> 05:43.995
YOU WANTED TO GO
TO A DRUG STORE?

05:44.039 --> 05:45.345
YEAH, I DO.

05:45.388 --> 05:46.781
THIS PLACE, THIS IS HEAVEN.

05:46.824 --> 05:48.391
THEY DON'T HAVE ANY
OF THIS STUFF IN AFGHANISTAN.

05:48.435 --> 05:50.350
HEY, IS THIS LADY SHAMPOO?

05:50.393 --> 05:51.612
OKAY.

05:51.655 --> 05:52.787
YOU KNOW WHAT YOU
ACTUALLY

05:52.830 --> 05:54.266
MISS THE MOST
WHILE YOU'RE OVER THERE?

05:54.310 --> 05:55.485
THIS IS GONNA SOUND INSANE.

05:55.529 --> 05:56.747
"BOUNCY HAIR
THAT HE WILL WANT

05:56.791 --> 05:58.445
TO RUN THIS FINGERS
THROUGH"?

05:58.488 --> 06:00.969
IT'S THE WAY GIRLS SMELL.

06:01.012 --> 06:03.232
IT DOESN'T ACTUALLY
SAY "HE'LL" ON IT.

06:03.275 --> 06:05.234
WELL, THIS IS THE SHAMPOO
THAT I USE.

06:05.277 --> 06:07.236
MMM.

06:07.279 --> 06:08.324
IT'S NICE.

06:08.368 --> 06:09.847
OKAY.
THIS IS NUTS. LET'S--

06:09.891 --> 06:12.241
OOH, SELF-CHECKOUT.NO.

06:12.284 --> 06:13.851
WE'VE LIVED TO SEE THE FUTURE.

06:13.895 --> 06:15.026
PLEASE DON'T DO THIS.

06:15.070 --> 06:17.202
SAM, SELF-CHECKOUT
IS THE BIGGEST SCAM.

06:17.246 --> 06:19.117
ARE YOU JOKING?
WHAT'S THE SCAM ABOUT?

06:19.161 --> 06:20.423
YOU THINK YOU'RE SAVING
ALL THIS TIME,

06:20.467 --> 06:22.294
BUT YOU REALLY AREN'T.NO, YOU ARE.

06:22.338 --> 06:23.339
THERE'S A REASON
WHY NO ONE WAS IN THIS LINE,

06:23.383 --> 06:25.123
'CAUSE THEY ALL ARE SMART.

06:25.167 --> 06:26.951
OKAY, NOW--

06:26.995 --> 06:27.909
[self-checkout machine]
PLEASE SCAN THE BAR CODE
OF YOUR FIRST ITEM.

06:27.952 --> 06:29.301
IT TALKS.

06:29.345 --> 06:30.912
WHERE ON MY ITEM
IS THE BAR CODE?

06:30.955 --> 06:34.089
I DON'T KNOW THIS ITEM--
OKAY, RIGHT THERE.

06:34.132 --> 06:35.569
YOU FOUND IT.

06:35.612 --> 06:37.048
[beep][self-checkout machine]
FIRST ITEM SCANNED.

06:37.092 --> 06:38.398
LOOK AT YOU.
YOU'RE A NATURAL.

06:38.441 --> 06:40.312
YOU GOT A SECOND CAREER.

06:40.356 --> 06:41.226
[machine]
PLEASE PLACE ITEM INTO BAG.

06:41.270 --> 06:43.098
I PLACED IT IN THE BAG.

06:43.141 --> 06:44.447
[machine]
PLEASE PLACE ITEM INTO BAG.

06:44.491 --> 06:46.144
I ALREADY DID THAT.

06:46.188 --> 06:48.016
[machine]
YOU HAVE NOT PLACED
AN ITEM INTO BAG.

06:48.059 --> 06:49.365
I'M SURE THERE'S,
LIKE, A BUTTON.

06:49.409 --> 06:50.801
[machine]
YOU ARE ATTEMPTING TO PLACE

06:50.845 --> 06:52.890
AN ITEM IN YOUR BAG
THAT HAS NOT BEEN PAID FOR.

06:52.934 --> 06:54.326
WE'RE NOT DOING THAT.I DIDN'T--WE'RE NOT--

06:54.370 --> 06:55.415
[machine]
SHOPLIFTING WILL BE PROSECUTED

06:55.458 --> 06:56.590
TO THE FULLEST EXTENT
OF THE LAW.

06:56.633 --> 06:58.069
THAT'S--THAT'S NOT
WHAT'S HAPPENING!

06:58.113 --> 06:59.288
DON'T GIVE US
THOSE JUDGMENTAL LOOKS.

06:59.331 --> 07:00.376
WE'RE TRYING TO SELF-CHECKOUT.

07:00.420 --> 07:01.812
GO BACK TO WAITING IN LINE!

07:01.856 --> 07:04.293
OKAY, I--
THAT'S INSANE.

07:04.336 --> 07:05.642
WHAT IS THIS ROBOT DOING?
OKAY, BAIL. BAIL.

07:05.686 --> 07:07.339
[machine]
THANK YOU, MANDY LAHIRI.

07:07.383 --> 07:08.471
PLEASE TAKE YOUR SHAMPOO.

07:08.515 --> 07:09.994
THIS IS SO MUCH FUN.

07:10.038 --> 07:11.300
I KNOW, IT'S GREAT.

07:11.343 --> 07:12.606
YOU KNOW WHAT WE SHOULD
DO NEXT WEEKEND?WHAT?

07:12.649 --> 07:14.172
WE SHOULD GO TO
THE MUMMY EXHIBIT AT THE MET.

07:14.216 --> 07:15.435
THE WALL IS REALLY LOW,

07:15.478 --> 07:16.697
SO YOU'RE NOT SUPPOSED
TO TOUCH THEM,

07:16.740 --> 07:18.089
BUT YOU CAN JUST, LIKE,
GET RIGHT IN THERE.

07:18.133 --> 07:19.047
LOOK, NOBODY CHECKS.

07:19.090 --> 07:20.396
WE'LL GET CURSED
IF THAT HAPPENS.

07:20.440 --> 07:21.832
YOU KNOW THAT, RIGHT?I HADN'T THOUGHT OF THAT.

07:21.876 --> 07:24.052
I'D ACTUALLY LIKE
TO DO THAT, BUT I CAN'T

07:24.095 --> 07:27.229
BECAUSE I'M GETTING READY
TO DEPLOY AGAIN

07:27.272 --> 07:28.360
FOR 18 MONTHS.

07:28.404 --> 07:31.363
SO YOU'RE NOT, LIKE,
BACK BACK?

07:31.407 --> 07:33.278
NO, I'M GONE, GONE.

07:33.322 --> 07:34.279
WHEN?

07:34.323 --> 07:35.890
NOT FOR A WHILE.

07:35.933 --> 07:37.413
TOMORROW.

07:40.982 --> 07:42.200
WHAT?

07:42.244 --> 07:43.201
I TOLD HIM GOOD LUCK,

07:43.245 --> 07:44.725
HAVE A NICE LIFE,

07:44.768 --> 07:46.204
AND CAME BACK TO WORK. [Morgan]
I'M SORRY.

07:46.248 --> 07:47.292
YOU CLEARED YOUR SCHEDULE

07:47.336 --> 07:49.120
TO RECONNECT
WITH THIS AWESOME GUY

07:49.164 --> 07:51.993
WHO KILLED OSAMA BIN LADEN,
WHO YOU THEN ABANDON

07:52.036 --> 07:53.081
IN THE MIDDLE
OF NEW YORK CITY?

07:53.124 --> 07:54.212
ARE YOU CRAZY?

07:54.256 --> 07:55.692
NO, I DIDN'T.
I DIDN'T ABANDON HIM.

07:55.736 --> 07:56.998
HMM.

07:57.041 --> 07:58.434
SAM IS KIND OF PERFECT.

07:58.478 --> 07:59.566
BUT I DON'T WANT TO BE
IN THE POSITION

07:59.609 --> 08:01.306
WHERE I'M HEARTBROKEN
OVER SOME GUY

08:01.350 --> 08:03.047
WHO'S NOT EVEN GONNA BE HERE
IN THE MORNING.

08:03.091 --> 08:04.484
THIS SOLDIER
DOESN'T FIT INTO

08:04.527 --> 08:06.094
YOUR "SEX AND THE CITY
FIND A HUSBAND" SCHEME,

08:06.137 --> 08:07.617
SO HE'S WORTHLESS
TO YOU NOW?

08:07.661 --> 08:09.053
DANNY, SOMETIMES I FEEL LIKE
YOU HAVE NEVER EVEN SEEN

08:09.097 --> 08:10.054
SEX AND THE CITY.

08:10.098 --> 08:11.752
I'VE SEEN AN EPISODE.

08:11.795 --> 08:14.581
ALL FOUR OF THEM WERE
WALKING DOWN THE STREET.

08:14.624 --> 08:16.234
REMIND ME TO NEVER LOSE TOUCH
WITH YOU

08:16.278 --> 08:18.454
AND RECONNECT WITH YOU
20 YEARS LATER.

08:18.498 --> 08:19.934
UGH.

08:19.977 --> 08:22.589
DID BETSY JUST TELL ME OFF?

08:22.632 --> 08:24.112
[tattoo gun buzzes]

08:24.155 --> 08:25.374
SAM.

08:25.417 --> 08:27.071
HEY, WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

08:27.115 --> 08:29.204
YOU SAID THAT YOU MIGHT
GET A TATTOO,

08:29.247 --> 08:31.119
SO THIS IS
THE FOURTH TATTOO PARLOR

08:31.162 --> 08:32.860
THAT I HAVE BEEN TO
IN THE VILLAGE.

08:32.903 --> 08:34.862
I HAVE SEEN
SOME THINGS PIERCED

08:34.905 --> 08:36.994
THAT I DID NOT KNOW
WERE PIERCEABLE.

08:37.038 --> 08:38.213
YOU KNOW WHAT,

08:38.256 --> 08:39.344
YOU DON'T NEED
TO HEAR THAT RIGHT NOW.

08:39.388 --> 08:40.998
THE POINT IS, SAM,
I REALLY LIKE YOU.

08:41.042 --> 08:43.348
FINDING A PERSON
YOU LIKE IS REALLY HARD.

08:43.392 --> 08:45.307
WOULDN'T YOU SAY?

08:45.350 --> 08:47.570
SO WE SHOULD SPEND ALL THE TIME
YOU HAVE LEFT TOGETHER.

08:47.614 --> 08:49.354
OKAY.
YEAH, I'D LOVE TO.

08:49.398 --> 08:50.355
LET'S GO.

08:50.399 --> 08:51.792
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

08:51.835 --> 08:53.315
WAIT, I'M NOT DONE
WITH YOUR TATTOO.

08:53.358 --> 08:55.535
OH, UH,
THAT'S OKAY.

08:55.578 --> 08:56.666
YOU KNOW, IT'S ACCURATE.

08:56.710 --> 08:58.581
NEXT.

08:58.625 --> 08:59.974
[Mindy]
SO WHAT ELSE DO YOU MISS
WHEN YOU'RE OVER THERE?

09:00.017 --> 09:02.977
NORMAL, EVERYDAY STUFF,
LIKE NAPPING ON THE COUCH.

09:03.020 --> 09:04.326
I MISS THAT A LOT.MM-HMM.

09:04.369 --> 09:06.154
I MISS SEX WITH A HUMAN.

09:06.197 --> 09:07.982
ALL RIGHT.YOU KNOW--
[laughs]

09:08.025 --> 09:09.200
YOU KNOW WHAT I MISS
THE MOST

09:09.244 --> 09:11.159
IS SEEING MOVIES
IN MOVIE THEATERS, HONESTLY.

09:11.202 --> 09:13.030
I SAW UPON A CRAP
SMART PHONE.

09:13.074 --> 09:14.684
YEAH?IT DIDN'T--IT WASN'T--

09:14.728 --> 09:16.730
I STILL CRIED,
BUT IT WASN'T THE SAME.

09:16.773 --> 09:18.122
YEAH.

09:18.166 --> 09:21.125
IF YOU MISS MOVIES,
I KIND OF HAVE A GREAT IDEA.

09:21.169 --> 09:23.084
"NORA EPHRON.

09:23.127 --> 09:24.694
DOUBLE FEATURE." YEAH.YEAH.

09:24.738 --> 09:27.001
'CAUSE I LOVE NORA EPHRON,

09:27.044 --> 09:28.393
AND TOM HANKS
IS YOUR THING.

09:28.437 --> 09:29.917
YOU LOVE TOM HANKS.

09:29.960 --> 09:32.093
I LOVE TOM HANKS?
EVERYBODY LOVES TOM HANKS.

09:32.136 --> 09:34.704
DON'T PUT THAT ON ME.
HE'S AMERICA'S FAVORITE ACTOR.

09:34.748 --> 09:36.053
NO, IT'S YOUR THING.

09:36.097 --> 09:37.577
COME ON, LET'S GO IN.

09:37.620 --> 09:40.841
DINNER OR A MOVIE...

09:40.884 --> 09:42.190
[crying]

09:42.233 --> 09:44.018
FOR AS LONG
AS WE BOTH SHALL LIVE?

09:45.106 --> 09:48.152
I COULDN'T HELP BUT SEE
YOUR FAX ON THE MACHINE,

09:48.196 --> 09:49.197
AND I COULDN'T HELP BUT NOTICE

09:49.240 --> 09:50.241
THAT THAT FAX IS
FROM A DONOR CLINIC,

09:50.285 --> 09:52.156
SO I COULDN'T HELP
BUT DEDUCE--

09:52.200 --> 09:53.375
YOU CAN HELP
ALL THOSE THINGS, OKAY?

09:53.418 --> 09:55.333
YEAH, WELL, YOU'RE GONNA
BE A DAD! COME HERE!

09:55.377 --> 09:56.334
[laughs]

09:56.378 --> 09:57.988
[Danny]
OKAY.

09:58.032 --> 09:59.511
[Morgan]
OH, MY GOD,
I'M JUST SAYING,

09:59.555 --> 10:01.078
THE NAME MORGAN WORKS
FOR BOYS OR GIRLS.

10:01.122 --> 10:02.558
BETTER FOR GIRLS.

10:02.602 --> 10:04.212
I'M JUST TRYING TO HELP
A COUPLE IN NEED. NO BIG DEAL.

10:04.255 --> 10:05.474
MORGAN,
DANNY'S ALWAYS GOING ON

10:05.517 --> 10:07.041
ABOUT HOW HE DOESN'T
WANT KIDS,

10:07.084 --> 10:09.043
WHICH I PERSONALLY THINK
IS A SHAME.

10:09.086 --> 10:12.220
YOU KNOW, THE WORLD NEEDS MORE
ROUGH-HEWN STRIVERS LIKE YOU.

10:12.263 --> 10:14.178
SCRUMMERS AND SCRAPPERS

10:14.222 --> 10:16.572
WHO CLAW AND SCRATCH THEIR WAY
THROUGH LIFE.

10:16.616 --> 10:18.095
[Betsy]
DR. CASTELLANO,
CAN YOU IMAGINE?

10:18.139 --> 10:19.662
ONE DAY, OUT OF THE BLUE,

10:19.706 --> 10:22.143
YOUR CHILD SHOWS UP
AT THE DOOR AND SAYS,

10:22.186 --> 10:23.448
"HI, I'M YOUR KID.

10:23.492 --> 10:25.102
I WANT TO HAVE A RELATIONSHIP
WITH YOU."

10:25.146 --> 10:27.191
MORE, LIKE,
"HEY, DAD, REMEMBER ME?

10:27.235 --> 10:28.062
BANG."

10:28.105 --> 10:29.280
[all groan]

10:29.324 --> 10:30.891
OH, MY GOD, BEVERLY,
DAMN IT.

10:30.934 --> 10:33.284
I DON'T GET WHY TOM HANKS
AND MEG RYAN

10:33.328 --> 10:34.895
EVEN DO MOVIES WITHOUT
THE OTHER IN THEM.

10:34.938 --> 10:36.070
I KNOW. IT'S TRUE.

10:36.113 --> 10:37.288
HE SHOULDN'T BE DOING THE DA VINCI CODE.

10:37.332 --> 10:39.682
LIKE, HE SHOULDN'T
DO FRANCHISES ALTOGETHER.

10:39.726 --> 10:40.944
HE IS THE FRANCHISE.

10:40.988 --> 10:43.077
WELL, I MEAN,
EXCEPT FOR TOY STORY.

10:43.120 --> 10:44.382
YES.

10:44.426 --> 10:45.557
THEY SHOULD DEFINITELY
KEEP MAKING THOSE MOVIES.

10:45.601 --> 10:46.950
THOSE WERE AMAZING.MM-HMM.

10:46.994 --> 10:47.951
HOOAH.

10:47.995 --> 10:49.257
HOOAH.

10:49.300 --> 10:50.693
WHERE'D YOU SERVE?

10:50.737 --> 10:53.435
THREE TOURS IN VIETNAM.
EVACUATION OF SAIGON.

10:53.478 --> 10:55.829
WHOA, THAT'S CRAZY.

10:55.872 --> 10:56.830
WHERE DID YOU SERVE?

10:56.873 --> 10:57.831
[Sam]
OH, JUST ONE TOUR IN IRAQ,

10:57.874 --> 10:59.093
ONE IN AFGHANISTAN.

10:59.136 --> 11:00.616
I'M ACTUALLY HEADING BACK
OUT THERE TOMORROW.

11:00.660 --> 11:01.791
WOW.

11:01.835 --> 11:03.750
NICE TO MEET YOU.YOU TOO. THANK YOU.

11:03.793 --> 11:04.751
KEEP YOUR HEAD DOWN.

11:04.794 --> 11:08.058
YEAH, I WILL.

11:10.365 --> 11:12.106
WHAT?

11:12.149 --> 11:14.848
[MGK's Lace Up]

11:14.891 --> 11:16.588
♪ SMASH THAT, SMASH THAT

11:16.632 --> 11:19.766
TAKE THIS OFF, TAKE THIS OFF.SO GLAD WE RAN INTO THAT GUY.

11:19.809 --> 11:23.117
♪ I'M AN EST BOY
TILL THE CASKET CLOSE ♪

11:24.640 --> 11:27.382
WELL, I GOT TO DO
EVERYTHING ON MY LIST.

11:27.425 --> 11:29.863
