WHO IS THIS LITTLE PERVERT

11:36.434 --> 11:38.262
THAT WAS WATCHING US
THE WHOLE TIME?

11:38.306 --> 11:40.308
HE'S NOT A PERVERT.
THAT'S BROWN BEAR.

11:40.351 --> 11:42.310
HE MUST HAVE SEEN A LOT OF DUDES
ROLL THROUGH THIS PIECE.

11:42.353 --> 11:44.399
WELL--A MARRIED GUY.

11:44.442 --> 11:45.705
WHAT?

11:45.748 --> 11:47.576
SURPRISING AMOUNT
OF BLACK GUYS.
BROWN BEAR!

11:47.619 --> 11:48.577
A WHOLE TEAM?

11:48.620 --> 11:50.361
HEY! HEY! THAT'S ENOUGH.

11:50.405 --> 11:52.146
SO HE LIKES TO SAY,
YOU KNOW, LIKE,

11:52.189 --> 11:54.191
"HEY, MINDY, WHAT ARE
YOUR HOPES AND DREAMS?"

11:54.235 --> 11:55.758
AND WHAT DO YOU SAY?

11:55.802 --> 11:58.761
LIKE, WELL, GET MARRIED TO
A NICE GUY WHO'S IN THE ARMY.

11:58.805 --> 12:00.458
[laughs] JEEZ,
I THINK BROWN BEAR SAYS,

12:00.502 --> 12:03.200
"WHOA, THAT IS NOT
WHAT A GUY WANTS TO HEAR

12:03.244 --> 12:04.941
RIGHT AFTER YOU HAVE SEX
WITH HIM, MINDY."

12:04.985 --> 12:06.943
[laughter]

12:06.987 --> 12:08.902
NO, COME ON.

12:08.945 --> 12:11.252
I'M SORRY.
OH, MAN.

12:11.295 --> 12:12.993
THIS SUCKS, SAM.

12:13.036 --> 12:14.124
WHY DOES IT SUCK?

12:14.168 --> 12:15.647
BECAUSE YOU'RE REALLY FUN,

12:15.691 --> 12:16.997
AND THEN YOU HAVE TO
LEAVE TOMORROW.

12:17.040 --> 12:19.390
I KNOW.
I WISH I WAS LESS FUN.

12:19.434 --> 12:21.349
AND I WISH I DIDN'T
HAVE TO LEAVE TOMORROW.

12:21.392 --> 12:24.961
WE DIDN'T EVEN GET TO DO ANY,
LIKE, FUN, DATE-Y THINGS.

12:25.005 --> 12:25.962
LIKE WHAT?

12:26.006 --> 12:27.137
LIKE, GO TO THE SUPERMARKET,

12:27.181 --> 12:29.052
AND HAVE A BIG FIGHT
IN FRONT OF PEOPLE.

12:29.096 --> 12:31.011
THAT SOUNDS FUN.

12:31.054 --> 12:32.708
PRETENDING LIKE I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO USE CHOPSTICKS,

12:32.752 --> 12:34.231
SO YOU CAN TEACH ME.

12:34.275 --> 12:36.668
HELP ME FIX MY AIR CONDITIONER
WHILE I HAND YOU TOOLS.

12:36.712 --> 12:38.192
I COULD DO THAT.

12:38.235 --> 12:39.846
REALLY?

12:39.889 --> 12:42.936
THIS MIGHT ACTUALLY BE
THE WORST DVD COLLECTION

12:42.979 --> 12:44.633
I'VE EVER SEEN
IN MY ENTIRE LIFE.

12:44.676 --> 12:46.853
SORRY THAT IT'S NOT ALL, LIKE,
CADDYSHACKOR WHATEVER.

12:46.896 --> 12:48.637
CADDYSHACK'SAN AMAZING FILM.

12:48.680 --> 12:51.509
I WOULD RATHER TAKE MY MCAT
AGAIN THAN WATCH CADDYSHACK.

12:51.553 --> 12:53.598
I ACTUALLY DON'T KNOW
IF I CAN GO BACK THERE

12:53.642 --> 12:56.340
AND FIGHT MY HEART OUT
KNOWING AN AMERICAN THINKS THAT.

12:56.384 --> 12:59.822
I FEEL THAT YOU HAVE NOT
SEEN CADDYSHACKRECENTLY.

12:59.866 --> 13:01.345
THE PROBLEM WITHCADDYSHACK
IS THAT PEOPLE FORGET

13:01.389 --> 13:03.521
THAT CADDYSHACK
IS ABOUT THE CADDIES.

13:03.565 --> 13:04.740
[distant thud]

13:04.784 --> 13:05.741
SAM?

13:05.785 --> 13:08.439
OH, MY GOD!
SAM! SAM!

13:13.183 --> 13:14.184
[Danny] HEY, WHAT'S UP?

13:14.228 --> 13:15.882
HEY.WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

13:15.925 --> 13:18.014
SAM WAS HELPING OUT
AROUND MY APARTMENT

13:18.058 --> 13:20.321
AND HE WAS DEFENESTRATED.

13:20.364 --> 13:22.323
YOU THREW A SOLDIER OUT
A WINDOW?

13:22.366 --> 13:23.803
WOW, ONE DAY WITH YOU,

13:23.846 --> 13:25.326
AND YOU MESSED HIM UP
WORSE THAN AL-QAEDA.

13:25.369 --> 13:26.718
HA HA HA, DANNY.

13:26.762 --> 13:28.242
I WOULD NOT JOKE
ABOUT AL-QAEDA.

13:28.285 --> 13:29.983
AND IT COULD HAVE
HAPPENED TO ANYBODY.

13:30.026 --> 13:31.462
HE'S FINE. HE'S JUST
A LITTLE, LIKE, BANGED UP.

13:31.506 --> 13:33.421
BUT I DO THINK
IT MIGHT MEAN

13:33.464 --> 13:35.379
THAT HE HAS TO DELAY
HIS DEPLOYMENT.

13:35.423 --> 13:36.685
YOU SOUND THRILLED.

13:36.728 --> 13:37.904
I AM.

13:37.947 --> 13:39.470
I WOULD LOVE TO BE ABLE
TO NURSE HIM BACK

13:39.514 --> 13:40.602
TO HEALTH FOR
A COUPLE OF WEEKS.

13:40.645 --> 13:41.995
YOU KNOW,
AND THE LAST COUPLE DAYS,

13:42.038 --> 13:44.127
MAYBE WE'RE, LIKE, IN VERMONT
AT A BED AND BREAK--

13:44.171 --> 13:45.433
I'M GLAD YOU'RE HERE

13:45.476 --> 13:47.827
'CAUSE I WANTED
TO ASK YOU ABOUT SOMETHING.

13:47.870 --> 13:49.480
IS IT FASHION-RELATED?
BECAUSE, DANNY,

13:49.524 --> 13:52.048
I MADE THE SICKEST LOOKBOOK
FOR YOU.

13:52.092 --> 13:53.876
WOULD YOU WEAR
A POCKET SQUARE?

13:53.920 --> 13:55.051
NO.

13:55.095 --> 13:58.446
I WANTED TO TALK TO YOU
ABOUT A COUPLE

13:58.489 --> 14:03.930
WHO ASKED ME TO BE
A SPERM DONOR.

14:03.973 --> 14:05.496
AND I SAID I'D DO IT.

14:05.540 --> 14:06.628
WAIT, WHAT?

14:06.671 --> 14:08.717
YEAH, I MEAN--

14:08.760 --> 14:10.240
I'M PROBABLY NEVER
GONNA HAVE KIDS

14:10.284 --> 14:12.155
SO WHY NOT DO IT NOW,
RIGHT?

14:12.199 --> 14:13.287
I'M SORRY.

14:13.330 --> 14:14.897
IF THAT IS THE REASON
YOU'RE DOING THIS,

14:14.941 --> 14:16.420
YOU DEFINITELY CANNOT DO IT.

14:16.464 --> 14:17.421
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

14:17.465 --> 14:19.249
ONE WEIRD WOMAN
BREAKS YOUR HEART,

14:19.293 --> 14:20.468
AND THEN ALL OF A SUDDEN,
YOU'RE LIKE,

14:20.511 --> 14:23.514
"NO, I DON'T KNOW
IF I CAN EVER BE A DAD.

14:23.558 --> 14:25.690
"I CAN NEVER BE
A FATHER FIGURE TO NO ONE

14:25.734 --> 14:27.301
WITH THIS BROKEN HEART
OF MINE."

14:27.344 --> 14:28.868
LIKE, THAT'S A BUNCH OF CRAP.

14:28.911 --> 14:30.957
YOU ALREADY CALL A WALLET
A BILLFOLD.

14:31.000 --> 14:32.393
YOU'RE GONNA BE A DAD, OKAY?

14:32.436 --> 14:33.742
JUST DEAL WITH IT.

14:33.785 --> 14:35.396
I ALREADY SAID I'D DO IT.

14:35.439 --> 14:36.440
OH.

14:36.484 --> 14:37.920
WELL, IF YOU ALREADY SAID

14:37.964 --> 14:39.487
THAT YOU WOULD DO
THIS LIFE-ALTERING DECISION

14:39.530 --> 14:41.184
OF BEING THE BIOLOGICAL FATHER

14:41.228 --> 14:42.490
OF SOME RANDOM KID
YOU DON'T KNOW,

14:42.533 --> 14:43.970
THEN, YEAH, I GUESS
YOU HAVE TO DO IT.

14:44.013 --> 14:45.754
REALLY?NO. OF COURSE NOT.

14:45.797 --> 14:46.973
YOU'RE SUCH A DUMMY.

14:47.016 --> 14:48.539
YOU KNOW WHAT?
I THINK I HAVE A LITTLE TIME.

14:48.583 --> 14:49.801
LET'S GO TRY TO GET
OUT OF THIS.

14:49.845 --> 14:51.368
[Mindy]
HERE'S THE DEAL.

14:51.412 --> 14:53.849
I KNOW DANNY
REALLY, REALLY WELL.

14:53.893 --> 14:55.416
WHOA, MINDY.
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE?

14:55.459 --> 14:56.547
